# ============================================================================
# Environment Configuration for Backup/Restore Script
# ============================================================================
#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Copy this file to .env in the same directory:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Edit .env and set your OpenSearch password:
#    nano .env  (or use your preferred editor)
#
# 3. The script will automatically load .env when you run it
#    No need to specify --env-file flag!
#
# 4. Secure your .env file:
#    chmod 600 .env
#
# ============================================================================

# OpenSearch Admin Password
# REQUIRED for production environments
# If not set, script will use default password with a warning
#
# Set this to your OpenSearch admin password:
# OPENSEARCH_PASSWORD=YourCustomPasswordHere

# ============================================================================
# USAGE EXAMPLES:
# ============================================================================
#
# After creating .env with your password, simply run:
#
# Backup:
#   ./backup-restore.sh export opensearch <app-name> opensearch.tar.gz
#   ./backup-restore.sh export digitize <app-name> digitize.tar.gz
#
# Restore:
#   ./backup-restore.sh import opensearch <app-name> opensearch.tar.gz
#   ./backup-restore.sh import digitize <app-name> digitize.tar.gz
#
# Override for single command:
#   OPENSEARCH_PASSWORD="TempPass" ./backup-restore.sh export opensearch rag-dev backup.tar.gz
#
# ============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES:
# ============================================================================
#
# ⚠️  IMPORTANT:
# 1. Never commit .env files with real passwords to version control
# 2. Ensure .env is in .gitignore
# 3. Use strong passwords in production (min 12 characters, mixed case, numbers, symbols)
# 4. Restrict file permissions: chmod 600 .env
# 5. Keep .env file in the same directory as the backup script
#
# ============================================================================